{{Jainism}}
Acharya '''Prem Suri''' was a [[Jainism|Jain]] Svetambar [[Murtipujaka]] Acharya. He belonged to the [[Tapa Gaccha]] sub-sect. After his death, his tradition was divided into two; led by [[Ramchandrasuri|Ram Chandra Suri]] and [[Bhuvan Bhanu Suri]] respectively. His tradition has the largest number of monks in [[Svetambara]] murtipujaka sect.

He was a disciple of Jain monk named Acharya Dansuriji. Along with [[Vijayanandsuri]], Dharma Vijay and Nitin Suri, he reformed ''Samvegi'' monks.<ref>{{cite book|last=Flügel|first=Peter|title=Studies in Jaina History and Culture: Disputes and Dialogues|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cAoLg0R1jZIC&pg=PA371|year=2006|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-0-203-00853-9|pages=312–398|chapter=Demographic Trends In Jaina Monasticism}}</ref>

